text: Anass Aït El Abdia (born 21 March 1993) is a Moroccan cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Continental team . He previously rode for UCI WorldTeam from 2017 until 2018. He was named in the startlist for the 2017 Vuelta a España, but he crashed out on stage 2. ==Major results== ;2013 : Les Challenges de la Marche Verte ::2nd Grand Prix Al Massira ::3rd Grand Prix Sakia El Hamra ;2014 : 1st Stage 5 Tour du Maroc ;2015 : 1st 20px Time trial, National Under-23 Road Championships : Challenge du Prince ::1st Trophée de la maison royale ::3rd Trophée princier ::3rd Trophée de l'anniversaire : 3rd Overall Tour du Maroc : Les Challenges de la Marche Verte ::3rd Grand Prix Oued Eddahab ::3rd Grand Prix Al Massira : 3rd Challenge des phosphates – Grand Prix de Khouribga ;2016 : 1st 20px Road race, National Road Championships : 6th Overall Tour de Côte d'Ivoire ;2017 : 1st 20px Overall Tour du Maroc ;2019 : 10th Prueba Villafranca de Ordizia ===Grand Tour general classification results timeline=== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" |- ! scope="col" | Grand Tour ! scope="col" | 2017 |- style="text-align:center;" ! scope="row" | alt=A pink jersey Giro d'Italia |— |- style="text-align:center;" ! scope="row" | alt=A yellow jersey Tour de France |— |- style="text-align:center;" ! scope="row" | alt=A red jersey Vuelta a España |DNF |} {| class="wikitable" |+ Legend |- ! scope="row" | — | Did not compete |- ! scope="row" | DNF | Did not finish |} ==References== ==External links== * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Moroccan male cyclists Category:Cyclists at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic cyclists of Morocco Category:Vuelta a España cyclists
